Package stackable

Defines valid types inside the main stack of a robot virtual machine (RVM)

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Stackable
    Stackable
    Simple interface to mark an element as being stackable (and thus being able to be put inside a robot main stack).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Addr
    Stackable - Addr
    Packs a number in an imutable way to be used as an address for jumps and function calls.
    Around
    Stackable - Around
    Provides the neighborhoods (set of terreins) for a given terrain.
    Attack
    Stackable - Attack
    Store one of the valid types of attacks supported by the game, encapsulating them in a stackable.
    Direction
    Stackable - Direction
    Stores the numerical representation of a direction, as used by the map to update positions.
    Num
    Stackable - Num
    Packs numbers inside a simple container, allowing them to be identified as stackables.
    Stack Deprecated
    Text
    Stackable - Text
    Packs strings inside a simple container, allowing them to be identified as stackables.
